779
00:46:03,949 --> 00:46:04,950
Taste it.

780
00:46:05,316 --> 00:46:06,714
Oh, no.

781
00:46:06,716 --> 00:46:09,047
Come on, try it.

782
00:46:09,049 --> 00:46:12,082
Taste the wild flavor straight from nature.

783
00:46:17,948 --> 00:46:19,146
It's good.

784
00:46:19,148 --> 00:46:20,815
Ah. You see?

785
00:46:28,650 --> 00:46:29,816
(JACQUES CHUCKLES)

786
00:46:31,350 --> 00:46:32,913
JACQUES: Mmm.

787
00:46:32,915 --> 00:46:34,849
- ANNE: Look at that.
- Yeah.

788
00:46:36,216 --> 00:46:38,047
ANNE: And this one here.

789
00:46:38,049 --> 00:46:41,584
So, you've just made a five-star picnic.

790
00:46:45,782 --> 00:46:46,783
Mmm.

791
00:46:47,983 --> 00:46:48,983
Wonderful.

792
00:46:50,617 --> 00:46:51,883
Try this.

793
00:46:53,616 --> 00:46:54,782
Oh, wait.

794
00:46:56,216 --> 00:46:57,783
This is so beautiful.

795
00:47:03,216 --> 00:47:04,550
Mmm.

796
00:47:06,182 --> 00:47:07,551
Delicious.

797
00:47:09,616 --> 00:47:10,982
But what about the car?

798
00:47:12,617 --> 00:47:13,950
She'll wait for us to eat.

799
00:47:15,183 --> 00:47:16,947
Try them all.

800
00:47:16,949 --> 00:47:18,114
Mmm.

801
00:47:18,116 --> 00:47:20,783
I don't need to try
everything to know what I like.

802
00:47:21,283 --> 00:47:22,650
(CHUCKLES)

803
00:47:23,082 --> 00:47:24,083
Mmm.

804
00:47:26,815 --> 00:47:29,081
It's the first time I tried Sudoku.

805
00:47:29,083 --> 00:47:30,779
I like it, but I got stuck.

806
00:47:30,781 --> 00:47:32,116
Teach me your tricks.

807
00:47:33,215 --> 00:47:37,046
You, um, look for triplets.

808
00:47:37,048 --> 00:47:39,046
(STUTTERS) You see the pattern?

809
00:47:39,048 --> 00:47:40,047
Yeah?

810
00:47:40,049 --> 00:47:42,083
You can find it when
you see three in a row.

811
00:47:51,315 --> 00:47:53,114
(EXHALES) I start puzzles,

812
00:47:53,116 --> 00:47:57,647
