994
00:58:13,047 --> 00:58:17,713
And, oh, you have to eat it with rissoles,

995
00:58:17,715 --> 00:58:20,013
potatoes fried in duck fat.

996
00:58:20,015 --> 00:58:23,816
And this is morel, mushrooms.

997
00:58:25,214 --> 00:58:26,981
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

998
00:58:29,214 --> 00:58:30,948
- Escargot!
- (CHUCKLES)

999
00:58:33,781 --> 00:58:37,847
That is a beautiful shawl,
Martine. Where did you get it?

1000
00:58:37,849 --> 00:58:40,679
It belonged to my Russian grandmother.

1001
00:58:40,681 --> 00:58:43,782
It's full of moth holes,
but I still love it.

1002
00:58:45,716 --> 00:58:49,882
Well, it's a beautiful
example of early-1900s paisley.

1003
00:58:50,947 --> 00:58:53,679
Well, if you're interested in fabrics,

1004
00:58:53,681 --> 00:58:56,346
