Oh.

1013
00:59:19,915 --> 00:59:21,647
(MARTINE AND JACQUES TALKING IN FRENCH)

1014
00:59:21,649 --> 00:59:23,113
ANNE: Hey!

1015
00:59:23,115 --> 00:59:27,614
Look at this exquisite embroidery
from the 18th century! Huh.

1016
00:59:27,616 --> 00:59:29,982
Can you believe it was all done by a man?

1017
00:59:31,981 --> 00:59:33,081
Of course it was.

1018
00:59:34,848 --> 00:59:36,945
Come see his picture.

1019
00:59:36,947 --> 00:59:37,948
Here he is!

1020
00:59:39,014 --> 00:59:40,015
(ANNE CHUCKLES)

1021
00:59:45,682 --> 00:59:47,246
(MARTINE SPEAKS FRENCH)

1022
00:59:47,248 --> 00:59:49,082
JACQUES: Mm-hmm.

1023
01:00:01,348 --> 01:00:03,649
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1024
01:00:04,181 --> 01:00:05,279
Oh, I'm sorry.

1025
01:00:05,281 --> 01:00:06,646
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1026
01:00:06,648 --> 01:00:08,615
- I'm sorry. Oh.
- (SPEAKING FRENCH)

1027
01:00:09,616 --> 01:00:11,650
(BOTH SPEAKING FRENCH)

1028
01:00:31,814 --> 01:00:35,549
(EXHALES) You're naughty
because I think you knew.

1029
01:00:37,815 --> 01:00:40,848
Well, I've got to go back to work.

1030
01:00:42,047 --> 01:00:46,245
Anne, don't be in a
hurry to go back to Paris.

1031
01:00:46,247 --> 01:00:49,116
You'll never forget your
travels with Jacques.

1032
01:00:50,381 --> 01:00:51,980
Trust me.

1033
01:00:51,982 --> 01:00:52,982
(CHUCKLES)

1034
01:00:54,214 --> 01:00:55,881
(BOTH SPEAKING FRENCH)

1035
01:00:58,014 --> 01:00:59,015
(MARTINE CHUCKLES)

1036
01:01:00,081 --> 01:01:01,082
(BOTH SPEAKING FRENCH)

1037
01:01:09,982 --> 01:01:11,846
(DOOR CLOSES)

1038
01:01:11,848 --> 01:01:13,882
That was a very touching goodbye.

1039
01:01:14,348 --> 01:01:15,980
Yeah.

1040
01:01:15,982 --> 01:01:17,113
MARTINE: Ooh.

1041
01:01:17,115 --> 01:01:21,212
I told her to get a pair
of sensible shoes. Hmm.

1042
01:01:21,214 --> 01:01:22,915
Of course you did.

1043
01:01:31,081 --> 01:01:34,614
Okay, Jacques. I've had enough detours.

1044
01:01:34,616 --> 01:01:36,979
It's straight to Paris now, right?

1045
01:01:36,981 --> 01:01:38,946
(JACQUES SIGHS)

1046
01:01:38,948 --> 01:01:41,549
Let's hear more of your music.

1047
01:01:46,115 --> 01:01:47,948
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

1048
01:01:50,214 --> 01:01:54,948
<i>♪ Fences in a row ♪</i>

1049
01:01:58,681 --> 01:02:01,781
<i>♪ Fences in a... ♪</i>

1050
01:02:14,981 --> 01:02:15,982
(DOOR CLOSES)

1051
01:02:34,348 --> 01:02:35,713
(ENGINE STARTS)

1052
01:02:35,715 --> 01:02:37,549
(POP ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

1053
01:02:39,814 --> 01:02:41,682
(SOOTHING CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

1054
01:03:29,947 --> 01:03:33,613
When I see the first new moon,

1055
01:03:33,615 --> 01:03:36,613
faint in the twilight...

1056
01:03:36,615 --> 01:03:40,379
I think of the moth eyebrows

1057
01:03:40,381 --> 01:03:43,881
of a girl I saw only once.

1058
01:03:44,314 --> 01:03:45,380
A haiku.

1059
01:03:45,382 --> 01:03:47,612
Nice.

1060
01:03:47,614 --> 01:03:49,945
The changing of the moon reminds me that

1061
01:03:49,947 --> 01:03:53,046
life and business have cycles.

1062
01:03:53,048 --> 01:03:55,549
JACQUES: Sometimes full, and sometimes not.

1063
01:03:56,681 --> 01:03:59,380
Hmm. You seem to live
as if it's always full.

1064
01:03:59,382 --> 01:04:00,746
(CHUCKLES)

1065
01:04:00,748 --> 01:04:02,212
Anne, I have to tell you that...

1066
01:04:02,214 --> 01:04:04,080
ANNE: Look! Vezelay!

1067
01:04:04,082 --> 01:04:05,213
Did you see the sign?

1068
01:04:05,215 --> 01:04:06,379
(CHUCKLES)

1069
01:04:06,381 --> 01:04:09,280
I had no idea we were so close.

1070
01:04:09,282 --> 01:04:13,145
Let's make a little detour and
see the beautiful cathedral there.

1071
01:04:13,147 --> 01:04:14,812
Who are you?

1072
01:04:14,814 --> 01:04:16,946
And what have you done
with my American friend

1073
01:04:16,948 --> 01:04:20,013
always in a hurry to get to Paris?

1074
01:04:20,015 --> 01:04:23,079
Don't I get a turn to choose a stop?

1075
01:04:23,081 --> 01:04:25,246
It's straight to Paris.

1076
01:04:25,248 --> 01:04:26,715
(MUSIC PLAYING)

1077
01:04:38,681 --> 01:04:42,149
ANNE: <i>Richard the Lionhearted
began the Third Crusade from here.</i>

1078
01:04:45,681 --> 01:04:47,581
(ORGAN MUSIC PLAYING)

1079
01:04:56,081 --> 01:04:57,678
ANNE: (WHISPERING) They say there are

1080
01:04:57,680 --> 01:04:59,881
bones of Mary Magdalene under the altar.

1081
01:05:02,314 --> 01:05:03,812
- <i>See those columns?</i>
- <i>Yes.</i>

1082
01:05:03,814 --> 01:05:06,081
ANNE: <i>Each one tells a story.</i>

1083
01:06:02,214 --> 01:06:04,748
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

1084
01:06:14,048 --> 01:06:15,881
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1085
01:06:27,648 --> 01:06:29,613
(ANNE CHUCKLES LIGHTLY)

1086
01:06:29,615 --> 01:06:31,849
You can tell me your sadness, Anne.

1087
01:06:36,314 --> 01:06:38,681
It happened a long time ago.

1088
01:06:39,681 --> 01:06:41,149
But it's still with you.

1089
01:06:42,315 --> 01:06:45,783
Yes. And it always will be.

1090
01:06:53,248 --> 01:06:54,682
David.

1091
01:06:56,247 --> 01:07:00,948
He had a heart defect,
and he lived only 39 days.

1092
01:07:04,948 --> 01:07:08,082
He was always surrounded by
nurses and doctors, but...

1093
01:07:09,082 --> 01:07:10,582
He knew me.

1094
01:07:12,681 --> 01:07:15,712
He held onto my finger...

1095
01:07:15,714 --> 01:07:19,046
And fought so hard
every minute of his life.

1096
01:07:19,048 --> 01:07:20,049
(SIGHS)

1097
01:07:26,081 --> 01:07:27,548
I'm so sorry.

1098
01:07:31,348 --> 01:07:33,848
(EXHALES) I thought I would die.

1099
01:07:35,680 --> 01:07:39,746
His father, my first husband...

1100
01:07:39,748 --> 01:07:41,916
He couldn't handle it, he left.

1101
01:07:43,082 --> 01:07:47,082
One day, I wandered into a church...

1102
01:07:48,349 --> 01:07:49,912
And there was an alcove

1103
01:07:49,914 --> 01:07:53,246
with the Virgin Mary
holding her infant son.

1104
01:07:53,248 --> 01:07:54,312
(INHALES DEEPLY)

1105
01:07:54,314 --> 01:07:59,146
And suddenly I felt connected...

1106
01:07:59,148 --> 01:08:02,814
To all the mothers who have
lost a child down through time.

1107
01:08:18,082 --> 01:08:21,613
I wear this to remind me

1108
01:08:21,615 --> 01:08:24,112
how fragile life is,

1109
01:08:24,114 --> 01:08:29,015
and how painful and
exquisite it is to be alive.

1110
01:08:35,214 --> 01:08:37,648
Anne, you're human.

1111
01:08:39,048 --> 01:08:41,949
And you've been to the
depths of what that means.

1112
01:08:59,814 --> 01:09:01,913
(JACQUES SPEAKING FRENCH)

1113
01:09:01,915 --> 01:09:04,049
Food is good for the soul.

1114
01:09:07,948 --> 01:09:11,079
This place is supposed
to be the best in Vezelay.

1115
01:09:11,081 --> 01:09:13,279
- Great.
- Please.

1116
01:09:13,281 --> 01:09:16,615
- Jacques, I need to make a phone call.
- Okay. Of course.

1117
01:09:24,081 --> 01:09:26,379
VOICEMAIL: <i>This is the
voicemail box for...</i>

1118
01:09:26,381 --> 01:09:28,046
MICHAEL: <i>Michael Lockwood.</i>

1119
01:09:28,048 --> 01:09:29,981
VOICEMAIL: <i>Please leave a message.</i>

1120
01:09:30,680 --> 01:09:32,678
Hey, honey, it's me.

1121
01:09:32,680 --> 01:09:34,446
I just miss you...

1122
01:09:34,448 --> 01:09:36,549
VOICEMAIL: <i>The mailbox is full and
cannot accept any messages at this...</i>

1123
01:09:39,981 --> 01:09:40,982
(SCOFFS)

1124
01:09:41,714 --> 01:09:43,581
(SIGHS) Man.

1125
01:09:45,081 --> 01:09:46,948
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1126
01:09:48,847 --> 01:09:50,679
JACQUES: Yes, of course.

1127
01:09:50,681 --> 01:09:53,779
Uh, listen, I need an advance. Yeah.

1128
01:09:53,781 --> 01:09:59,679
Come on, you know our new picture
will be a big hit in the UK.

1129
01:09:59,681 --> 01:10:01,748
No, I need the money now, damn it!

1130
01:10:09,081 --> 01:10:10,681
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1131
01:10:12,680 --> 01:10:14,612
You'll drink for both of us.

1132
01:10:14,614 --> 01:10:15,881
We still have a long drive.

1133
01:10:17,681 --> 01:10:22,582
It's a Cuvee Silex, from
Domaine Daguenau 2012.

1134
01:10:23,614 --> 01:10:25,112
Of course.

1135
01:10:25,114 --> 01:10:26,945
<i>Merci.</i>

1136
01:10:26,947 --> 01:10:31,746
It has a crisp mineral note
that expresses, uh, the terroir.

1137
01:10:31,748 --> 01:10:37,080
And the vineyard subsoil
is calcareous chalk.

1138
01:10:37,082 --> 01:10:40,679
It's giving something
really special for this wine.

1139
01:10:40,681 --> 01:10:43,082
Because it's very deep and, uh...

1140
01:10:43,947 --> 01:10:45,312
I am boring you.

1141
01:10:45,314 --> 01:10:47,311
No. No, no.

1142
01:10:47,313 --> 01:10:49,115
I mean, yes.

1143
01:10:49,881 --> 01:10:51,212
(CHUCKLES)

1144
01:10:51,214 --> 01:10:53,945
It's just a little intimidating,
how much you know about wine.

1145
01:10:53,947 --> 01:10:55,112
It's just knowing what you like.

1146
01:10:55,114 --> 01:10:57,882
My happiest memories are around the table.

1147
01:10:59,815 --> 01:11:02,715
And I'm here now with you.

1148
01:11:09,082 --> 01:11:10,082
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

1149
01:11:12,081 --> 01:11:13,982
Excuse me. (CLEARS THROAT)

1150
01:11:19,982 --> 01:11:21,446
What's wrong?

1151
01:11:21,448 --> 01:11:25,582
It's Alex. She's decided to go
camping with friends for her birthday.

1152
01:11:28,047 --> 01:11:31,748
It'll be the first birthday in
her life that I won't be with her.

1153
01:11:36,880 --> 01:11:39,245
You've taught her how
to be happy on her own.

1154
01:11:39,247 --> 01:11:42,815
Now it's your turn. And you're in Burgundy.

1155
01:11:44,780 --> 01:11:46,081
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1156
01:11:54,015 --> 01:11:55,079
(CHUCKLES)

1157
01:11:55,081 --> 01:11:56,712
<i>Merci.</i>

1158
01:11:56,714 --> 01:11:59,346
(LAUGHS) Look at this.

1159
01:11:59,348 --> 01:12:02,678
No, it's good, but who needs this fuss?

1160
01:12:02,680 --> 01:12:05,112
I remember going into the garden

1161
01:12:05,114 --> 01:12:07,045
with my mother and picking tomatoes...

1162
01:12:07,047 --> 01:12:09,912
Really ripe, red ones in August.

1163
01:12:09,914 --> 01:12:11,612
Bringing them into the kitchen,

1164
01:12:11,614 --> 01:12:13,945
still warm from the sun.

1165
01:12:13,947 --> 01:12:16,080
She'd put slices on fresh bread,

1166
01:12:16,082 --> 01:12:20,913
add good olive oil, sea salt
and fresh ground pepper and say,

1167
01:12:20,915 --> 01:12:23,682
"Jacques, you'll never eat better."

1168
01:12:25,313 --> 01:12:27,078
She was right.

1169
01:12:27,080 --> 01:12:29,713
The best food in the world
is straight from the garden

1170
01:12:29,715 --> 01:12:33,879
with very little done to
it. Authentic, like you.

1171
01:12:33,881 --> 01:12:34,882
(CHUCKLES)

1172
01:12:40,380 --> 01:12:41,981
So, what did your family eat, Anne?

1173
01:12:43,648 --> 01:12:45,946
I grew up in Cleveland. (LAUGHS)

1174
01:12:45,948 --> 01:12:48,079
Nobody's perfect. (CHUCKLES)

1175
01:12:48,081 --> 01:12:50,845
No, our idea of fine
dining was fried chicken,

1176
01:12:50,847 --> 01:12:54,312
mashed potatoes, and frozen peas.

1177
01:12:54,314 --> 01:12:58,345
I didn't learn about good food
until I went to California.

1178
01:12:58,347 --> 01:13:01,244
There is one thing from my
past that I make well, though.

1179
01:13:01,246 --> 01:13:02,945
Lemon meringue pie.

1180
01:13:02,947 --> 01:13:05,013
Mmm, great.

1181
01:13:05,015 --> 01:13:08,078
Sometimes I think Michael
married me for my pie. (CHUCKLES)

1182
01:13:08,080 --> 01:13:09,948
He married you for much more than your pie.

1183
01:13:12,080 --> 01:13:13,981
(WAITER SPEAKING FRENCH)

1184
01:13:17,347 --> 01:13:18,681
JACQUES: <i>Merci.</i>

1185
01:13:22,680 --> 01:13:25,813
This butter from Brittany is
the best we have in France.

1186
01:13:25,815 --> 01:13:28,111
Now, there is a trip we should take.

1187
01:13:28,113 --> 01:13:33,945
The coastline, the oysters, the cider,
and <i>les galettes bretonnes...</i>

1188
01:13:33,947 --> 01:13:38,078
Those wide and thin
buckwheat pancakes. Mmm.

1189
01:13:38,080 --> 01:13:40,681
- (CELL PHONE RINGING)
- (CHUCKLES) I love pancakes.

1190
01:13:42,348 --> 01:13:43,645
Excuse me.

1191
01:13:43,647 --> 01:13:45,678
Thank you.

1192
01:13:45,680 --> 01:13:47,645
- Michael!
- MICHAEL: <i>Everything okay?</i>

1193
01:13:47,647 --> 01:13:49,845
Yeah, I was just checking
in to see what's...

1194
01:13:49,847 --> 01:13:53,211
<i>I think I'm over this
whole producing thing.</i>

1195
01:13:53,213 --> 01:13:54,779
<i>Once Alex is out of school,</i>

1196
01:13:54,781 --> 01:13:56,045
<i>let's talk about Plan B.</i>

1197
01:13:56,047 --> 01:13:57,312
Oh.

1198
01:13:57,314 --> 01:13:58,678
<i>Honey, there are problems
on the Morocco shoot.</i>

1199
01:13:58,680 --> 01:14:03,012
<i>I have to go there ASAP with
a big fire extinguisher.</i>

1200
01:14:03,014 --> 01:14:06,645
Huh. Well, when would
that put you in Paris?

1201
01:14:06,647 --> 01:14:09,212
<i>I can hardly hear
you. Where are you?</i>

1202
01:14:09,214 --> 01:14:11,211
I'm in a restaurant.

1203
01:14:11,213 --> 01:14:12,612
<i>With Jacques?</i>

1204
01:14:12,614 --> 01:14:13,678
Well, yeah.

1205
01:14:13,680 --> 01:14:15,147
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1206
01:14:17,981 --> 01:14:19,147
<i>Listen, Anne.</i>

1207
01:14:20,780 --> 01:14:22,445
<i>Jacques can be very charming,</i>

1208
01:14:22,447 --> 01:14:25,648
<i>and Frenchmen have no scruples
when it comes to married women.</i>

1209
01:14:30,313 --> 01:14:32,613
I'll keep that in mind.

1210
01:14:32,615 --> 01:14:34,849
<i>Call me as soon as you
get to the apartment.</i>

1211
01:14:35,680 --> 01:14:36,978
<i>Love you.</i>

1212
01:14:36,980 --> 01:14:38,080
Love you, too.

1213
01:14:46,881 --> 01:14:47,882
(EXHALES)

1214
01:14:48,781 --> 01:14:49,849
Hmm.

1215
01:14:53,915 --> 01:14:55,781
JACQUES: "Nipples of Venus."

1216
01:14:57,180 --> 01:14:59,011
It's their specialty.

1217
01:14:59,013 --> 01:15:00,015
JACQUES: <i>Merci.</i>

1218
01:15:08,347 --> 01:15:10,781
Mmm. Mmm-hmm.

1219
01:15:12,313 --> 01:15:13,849
Oh, my goodness.

1220
01:15:16,246 --> 01:15:17,882
(CHUCKLES)

1221
01:15:21,847 --> 01:15:23,814
You've been taking a lot of photos.

1222
01:15:24,814 --> 01:15:26,712
Let me see what you've got there.

1223
01:15:26,714 --> 01:15:28,178
Oh, they're nothing, really.

1224
01:15:28,180 --> 01:15:30,114
Come on. Show me.

1225
01:15:49,381 --> 01:15:51,115
You have a beautiful eye for detail.

1226
01:15:53,614 --> 01:15:56,179
They are very evocative.

1227
01:15:56,181 --> 01:15:57,613
You think?

1228
01:15:57,615 --> 01:15:59,012
Yeah. You don't show the whole thing.

1229
01:15:59,014 --> 01:16:03,079
You make me imagine the complete picture.

1230
01:16:03,081 --> 01:16:04,244
Do you make prints?

1231
01:16:04,246 --> 01:16:05,712
- No.
- (DISTANT CHEERING)

1232
01:16:05,714 --> 01:16:07,211
Although I've thought of making

1233
01:16:07,213 --> 01:16:10,681
some large prints of a few images.

1234
01:16:11,181 --> 01:16:12,549
Hmm.

1235
01:16:16,114 --> 01:16:18,212
What does Michael think of your photos?

1236
01:16:18,214 --> 01:16:19,278
I haven't really shown him.

1237
01:16:19,280 --> 01:16:20,778
Why not?

1238
01:16:20,780 --> 01:16:23,346
I don't think he sees me as a photographer.

1239
01:16:23,348 --> 01:16:27,244
I mean, he asks to see them,
but I think he's just being nice.

1240
01:16:27,246 --> 01:16:29,813
Michael is a nice guy.

1241
01:16:29,815 --> 01:16:31,812
Why are you not revealing yourself

1242
01:16:31,814 --> 01:16:35,081
to the man you've been with for 20 years?

1243
01:16:42,213 --> 01:16:43,612
See?

1244
01:16:43,614 --> 01:16:46,613
How beautiful you are.

1245
01:16:46,615 --> 01:16:47,981
(LOUD CHEERING IN THE BACKGROUND)

1246
01:16:49,615 --> 01:16:51,612
It's a wedding.

1247
01:16:51,614 --> 01:16:53,813
(ACCORDION MUSIC PLAYING)

1248
01:16:57,813 --> 01:16:59,814
- I like this music.
- Yeah?

1249
01:17:03,080 --> 01:17:04,613
Oh.

1250
01:17:04,615 --> 01:17:05,782
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

1251
01:17:07,281 --> 01:17:09,179
ANNE: Oh...

1252
01:17:09,181 --> 01:17:11,948
Let's pretend we are in that Renoir
painting, <i>Danse a Bougival.</i>

1253
01:17:13,213 --> 01:17:14,312
JACQUES: <i>Yeah?</i>

1254
01:17:14,314 --> 01:17:15,681
ANNE: <i>Okay.</i> (LAUGHS)

1255
01:17:17,280 --> 01:17:19,147
(BOTH LAUGH)

1256
01:17:20,981 --> 01:17:21,981
Okay.

1257
01:17:32,347 --> 01:17:34,880
(MUSIC PLAYING)

1258
01:17:46,314 --> 01:17:47,781
(MAN SPEAKING FRENCH)

1259
01:17:50,680 --> 01:17:52,814
(ALL SPEAKING FRENCH)

